They are like that. One must not hold it against them. Children should 
always show great forbearance toward grown-up people.

But certainly, for us who understand life, figures are a matter of indefference.
I should have liked to begin this story in the fashion of the fairy tales.
I should have liked to say: "Once upon a time there was a little prince 
who lived on a planet that was scarely any bigger than himself, and who had need of sheep..."
